problems we see is people failing to remove the green protective cap from the

77
00:05:40,709 --> 00:05:45,279
pyranometer. The green cap is designed for protection of the lens when you are

78
00:05:45,279 --> 00:05:49,089
transporting or storing your pyranometer but needs to be removed when

79
00:05:49,089 --> 00:05:53,979
you're taking readings. A quick and easy check of sensor functionality can be

80
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:57,830
determined using a voltmeter with millivolt resolution. Connect the

81
00:05:57,829 --> 00:06:01,490
positive lead of the voltmeter to the red wire from the sensor and the

82
00:06:01,490 --> 00:06:06,960
negative lead or common to the black wire from the sensor. Direct the sensor's diffuser

83
00:06:06,959 --> 00:06:11,019
toward a light source and verify this sensor provides a signal. Blocking all

84
00:06:11,019 --> 00:06:16,000
radiation from the sensor should force the sensor signal to read 0. Finally, if you have

